343
00:17:47,132 --> 00:17:50,124
And I found out later
they had touched up the photo

344
00:17:50,235 --> 00:17:54,171
so it wasn't as bad
as what it really was.

345
00:17:56,675 --> 00:18:00,475
And you're just going,
"What happened?

346
00:18:00,579 --> 00:18:02,513
What happened to Amelia?

347
00:18:02,614 --> 00:18:04,912
Why does her face
look like that?"

348
00:18:06,852 --> 00:18:10,049
They couldn't tell me.
They didn't say anything.

349
00:18:10,155 --> 00:18:15,491
It was weeks... weeks...
before the medical <i>examiner...</i>

350
00:18:15,594 --> 00:18:18,085
It was August.
Second week in August.

351
00:18:18,197 --> 00:18:22,258
But the police told us kind of
what happened a week later.

352
00:18:22,367 --> 00:18:25,803
"She died peacefully
on the couch, " they said.

353
00:18:25,904 --> 00:18:27,963
You don't die peacefully
on the couch

354
00:18:28,073 --> 00:18:31,668
and have this horrendous wound
on your head.

355
00:18:31,777 --> 00:18:35,907
She would have had to recover
from a concussion had she lived.

356
00:18:36,014 --> 00:18:39,279
The medical examiner said
it could have been caused

357
00:18:39,384 --> 00:18:40,874
by when she passed out.

358
00:18:40,986 --> 00:18:43,147
Hitting the kitchen floor.

359
00:18:43,255 --> 00:18:46,816
I think it was caused
by something entirely different.

360
00:18:46,925 --> 00:18:48,916
The cops ended up
coming to my house,

361
00:18:49,027 --> 00:18:52,793
