a tattoo artist

497
00:26:56,615 --> 00:26:59,140
and own a tattoo parlor
at one time.

498
00:26:59,250 --> 00:27:00,717
So I went
and had a tattoo put on.

499
00:27:00,819 --> 00:27:02,309
This is supposed to be C. B. B.,

500
00:27:02,420 --> 00:27:05,981
but I think it's a little
infected at the moment.

501
00:27:06,091 --> 00:27:08,559
This picture was taken
in Africa.

502
00:27:08,660 --> 00:27:13,063
We had it blown up
and had it down at his wake.

503
00:27:13,164 --> 00:27:16,827
I mean, we had a celebration of
his life rather than a funeral.

504
00:27:16,935 --> 00:27:18,334
<i>And...</i>

505
00:27:20,205 --> 00:27:23,572
There was every kind
of kid and parent there.

506
00:27:25,176 --> 00:27:27,474
From all walks of life.
From <i>all...</i>

507
00:27:30,148 --> 00:27:32,548
Every different kind
of dress <i>and...</i>

508
00:27:33,852 --> 00:27:36,514
<i>...</i> every different kind
of parent.

509
00:27:36,621 --> 00:27:38,145
That's what he taught us,
though,

510
00:27:38,256 --> 00:27:40,554
is acceptance, you know?

511
00:27:40,659 --> 00:27:44,789
He just wanted people
to be accepted for who they are

512
00:27:44,896 --> 00:27:47,160
and how they were
or how they dressed.

513
00:27:47,265 --> 00:27:48,425
Somebody who uses drugs

514
00:27:48,533 --> 00:27:51,195
isn't just hanging out
in a dark corner

515
00:27:51,302 --> 00:27:52,530
with just a few people,
you know?

516
00:27:52,637 --> 00:27:54,264
It can be anybody.

517
00:27:56,675 --> 00:27:58,108
We were actually in Phoenix.

518
00:27:58,209 --> 00:27:59,540
We had gotten back from Africa,

519
00:27:59,644 --> 00:28:01,703
and we'd left him home alone
to be with his sister.

520
00:28:01,813 --> 00:28:04,373
She was watching him,
and David and I were in Phoenix.

521
00:28:04,482 --> 00:28:08,316
And he had gone to work that
night, was supposed to be home.

522
00:28:08,420 --> 00:28:10,479
And Brianne got a phone call.

523
00:28:10,588 --> 00:28:12,522
He didn't come home at noon?
Or midnight.

524
00:28:12,624 --> 00:28:14,353
He was supposed to be home
by midnight.

525
00:28:14,459 --> 00:28:18,452
And apparently he had bought
some cocaine the night before

526
00:28:18,563 --> 00:28:20,292
with a group of kids.

527
00:28:20,398 --> 00:28:25,700
He had driven to Sugarhouse
and bought a rock.

528
00:28:25,804 --> 00:28:27,635
He came home alone,

529
00:28:27,739 --> 00:28:29,536
did the coke
for whatever reason.

530
00:28:29,641 --> 00:28:32,371
What made him do it, why he
wanted to do it that <i>night...</i>

531
00:28:32,477 --> 00:28:35,310
'Cause we thought he was
pretty drug-free at that point.

532
00:28:35,413 --> 00:28:40,646
And he brought it home,
did it himself at home.

533
00:28:40,752 --> 00:28:41,810
He was alone.

534
00:28:41,920 --> 00:28:43,820
He got in the bathtub.

535
00:28:43,922 --> 00:28:49,258
They said maybe the heat on top
of the coke took his life.

536
00:28:49,360 --> 00:28:51,294
They found him in the bathtub.

537
00:28:51,396 --> 00:28:53,591
Found him
in the upstairs bathroom.

538
00:28:56,534 --> 00:28:58,798
Just white as a sheet.

539
00:28:58,903 --> 00:29:02,737
And I knew when I first saw him
that he was gone.

540
00:29:02,841 --> 00:29:07,175
And my son and Bree
were out in the car.

541
00:29:07,278 --> 00:29:08,643
The hardest thing
I've ever had to do

542
00:29:08,747 --> 00:29:12,706
was go out and tell Bree
that her brother had died.

543
00:29:12,817 --> 00:29:16,651
Our son was Colton Ben Berger.

544
00:29:16,755 --> 00:29:20,452
Born on April 8, 1989.

545
00:29:20,558 --> 00:29:24,426
He passed away of
an accidental overdose of drugs

546
00:29:24,529 --> 00:29:27,760
on January 28, 2006.

547
00:29:29,434 --> 00:29:36,772
I think his real aspiration
in life was to help people.

548
00:29:38,543 --> 00:29:40,170
And he'll <i>never...</i>

549
00:29:40,278 --> 00:29:41,575
Excuse me.
I'm sorry.

550
00:29:41,679 --> 00:29:43,738
<i>...</i> have the chance to do that.

551
