I could probably walk into
any high school in this state

552
00:29:52,657 --> 00:29:56,923
and find it within five minutes.

553
00:29:57,028 --> 00:29:59,496
You know, the problem is,
is that everybody's doing them.

554
00:29:59,597 --> 00:30:01,656
Kids that were the stoners.
People in band.

555
00:30:01,800 --> 00:30:03,358
Computer nerds.
The football team.

556
00:30:03,468 --> 00:30:05,368
You know, just normal,
unsuspecting kids

557
00:30:05,470 --> 00:30:07,802
that you just expect to be
good high school students

558
00:30:07,906 --> 00:30:10,568
that were all on
these crazy drugs.

559
00:30:10,675 --> 00:30:12,540
I have yet to find
a high school,

560
00:30:12,644 --> 00:30:14,407
public or private,

561
00:30:14,512 --> 00:30:16,878
that does not have
drugs accessible

562
00:30:16,981 --> 00:30:20,508
and that there is not
active drug use going on.

563
00:30:20,618 --> 00:30:23,348
If you were a new student
in a new high school,

564
00:30:23,454 --> 00:30:26,685
and you really wanted
to find any of these drugs,

565
00:30:26,791 --> 00:30:28,418
I would bet that
it would take you

566
00:30:28,526 --> 00:30:30,357
just a matter of hours.

567
00:30:30,461 --> 00:30:32,952
When this was going on, I said,
"We're gonna change schools.

568
00:30:33,064 --> 00:30:34,429
It's just that simple."

569
00:30:34,532 --> 00:30:36,727
And he said, "You know, Dad,

570
00:30:36,835 --> 00:30:40,828
you can get drugs anywhere,
anytime you want."

571
00:30:49,747 --> 00:30:52,511
This person writes,
"Your life brought us life.

572
00:30:52,617 --> 00:30:54,050
Hope you're running naked
in heaven.

573
00:30:54,152 --> 00:30:56,052
I love you and miss you.
Kyle."

574
00:31:31,589 --> 00:31:33,955
I'll eat my hat
if I find the drug addict

575
00:31:34,058 --> 00:31:35,548
that's not addicted to sugar.

576
00:31:35,660 --> 00:31:37,719
If you are always
on a high-sugar food,

577
00:31:37,829 --> 00:31:39,854
you know that if
you're a little depressed

578
00:31:39,964 --> 00:31:41,829
and a little blue
and a little tired,

579
00:31:41,966 --> 00:31:44,594
all you have to go
is eat a bunch of M & M's

580
00:31:44,702 --> 00:31:49,662
and a lot of soda pop, with
caffeine in it, if possible.

581
00:31:49,774 --> 00:31:53,938
And so you're already training
your body to look at food

582
00:31:54,045 --> 00:31:57,776
as a pharmaceutical way
to whip a dead horse.

583
00:31:57,882 --> 00:32:02,478
And I think the next stage
might be prescription drugs.

584
00:32:02,587 --> 00:32:04,578
And I think we need
to look at it.

585
00:32:04,689 --> 00:32:07,487
I think we're a nation
in deep, deep distress.

586
00:32:07,592 --> 00:32:11,426
If we want to truly help
drug addicts,

587
00:32:11,529 --> 00:32:14,054
I think we need to look
at the nutritional aspect.

588
00:32:14,165 --> 00:32:17,760
Is it the mind or the body?
I think it's both.

589
00:32:17,869 --> 00:32:21,635
And a body will not work well
with poor food.

590
00:32:21,739 --> 00:32:24,401
I personally almost
became addicted to painkillers

591
00:32:24,509 --> 00:32:25,533
when I got hurt.

592
00:32:25,643 --> 00:32:30,376
Because 2:00 in the morning,
it numbs your emotional pain,

593
00:32:30,481 --> 00:32:31,743
as well as your physical pain.

594
00:32:31,849 --> 00:32:33,714
And then as
the physical pain lessens,

595
00:32:33,818 --> 00:32:36,514
the emotional pain
can pretty much stay the same.

596
00:32:36,621 --> 00:32:39,385
And, you know, that pill makes
the emotional pain go away.

597
00:32:39,490 --> 00:32:40,855
I had a really good doctor,

598
00:32:40,959 --> 00:32:42,950
and he probably stopped me
just a couple pills away

599
00:32:43,061 --> 00:32:45,029
from becoming addicted
to the painkillers.

600
00:32:45,129 --> 00:32:47,962
So now I have to be really,
really careful with them.

601
00:32:48,066 --> 00:32:51,900
And now I prefer...
Food is my addiction of choice.

602
00:32:52,003 --> 00:32:53,630
How does that work for you?

603
00:32:53,738 --> 00:32:55,103
Well,
from a disability standpoint,

604
00:32:55,206 --> 00:32:56,605
it's a major drawback.

605
00:32:56,708 --> 00:32:59,006
Because it makes everything
I have to do more difficult

606
00:32:59,110 --> 00:33:02,739
'cause I'm trying to move a
large body with just half my...

607
00:33:02,847 --> 00:33:04,405
with just my arms.

608
00:33:04,515 --> 00:33:06,005
And, so, I love my food.

609
00:33:06,117 --> 00:33:08,984
I n a way, it's my best friend,
and it's my worst enemy.

610
00:33:28,606 --> 00:33:31,769
You know, when I walk in,
and I see 20 different <i>people...</i>

611
00:33:31,876 --> 00:33:35,676
And to me, they're just
20 different people.

612
00:33:35,780 --> 00:33:37,680
But when you start
to get to know them,

613
00:33:37,782 --> 00:33:39,010
they're 20 people you love.

614
00:33:39,117 --> 00:33:41,108
And they're all so different.

615
00:33:41,219 --> 00:33:44,017
And if that could be
outside of here,

616
00:33:44,122 --> 00:33:47,990
we wouldn't feel
so rotten about ourselves.

617
00:33:48,092 --> 00:33:49,957
And the guilt.

618
00:33:53,331 --> 00:33:57,097
There was a time
I ruined a business,

619
00:33:57,201 --> 00:33:58,964
moved back in with my parents.

620
00:33:59,070 --> 00:34:01,061
So now and then,
I'd go get a hotel room.

621
00:34:01,172 --> 00:34:03,732
Just so I could go drink.

622
00:34:03,841 --> 00:34:05,775
And I remember one time

623
00:34:05,877 --> 00:34:08,038
feeling so guilty
about what I was doing,

624
00:34:08,146 --> 00:34:09,613
I couldn't sleep
in the hotel room.

625
00:34:09,714 --> 00:34:10,908
I went out and slept
in my truck.

626
00:34:11,015 --> 00:34:14,075
'Cause I didn't feel I deserved
to sleep on that bed,

627
00:34:14,185 --> 00:34:15,709
with the TV and all that.

628
00:34:15,820 --> 00:34:17,014
Where does that come from?

629
00:34:17,121 --> 00:34:18,713
The upbringing here?
What is it?

630
00:34:18,823 --> 00:34:20,154
Oh, definitely.

631
00:34:21,692 --> 00:34:24,855
You know, Happy Valley
and Guilt Valley.

632
00:34:24,962 --> 00:34:27,658
I mean, the guilt <i>is...</i>

633
00:34:29,834 --> 00:34:31,563
My sister has moved
to California,

634
00:34:31,669 --> 00:34:33,159
and she won't come back
because of it.

635
00:34:33,271 --> 00:34:37,833
She doesn't want to be judged
for every little thing she does.

636
00:34:37,942 --> 00:34:41,639
I think everybody in this state
needs to look in the mirror

637
00:34:41,746 --> 00:34:43,714
and quit looking
through the windows.

638
00:35:10,208 --> 00:35:12,739
You'd be surprised
how much gas this uses

639
00:35:12,844 --> 00:35:16,075
and how much...
we'll call him "Greg"...

640
00:35:16,180 --> 00:35:18,671
how much gas his car uses.

641
00:35:20,251 --> 00:35:22,151
I don't know if you can see him
up in his car,

642
00:35:22,253 --> 00:35:24,278
but Greg's got one of these
little weighted deals.

643
00:35:24,388 --> 00:35:27,050
And when you're sick
and you're anticipating going up

644
00:35:27,158 --> 00:35:28,682
and getting drugs or whatever,

645
00:35:28,793 --> 00:35:31,990
he takes his little deal

646
00:35:32,096 --> 00:35:34,894
and he does
these reverse tricep curls

647
00:35:34,999 --> 00:35:37,365
to take his mind
off this whole process

648
00:35:37,468 --> 00:35:38,730
of being sick and going up.

649
00:35:38,836 --> 00:35:42,602
It's just something to do to
keep you occupied kind of thing.

650
00:35:42,707 --> 00:35:46,108
Because I'll meet him sometimes,
and he's just...

651
00:35:46,210 --> 00:35:50,613
I mean, just shaking.
Just shaking like a leaf.

652
00:35:50,715 --> 00:35:53,980
When I'm out of
doctor-prescribed pain medicine,

653
00:35:54,085 --> 00:35:57,111
then I'll have to go a few days
or a week or whatever

654
00:35:57,221 --> 00:35:59,917
of doing this, you know?

655
00:36:02,760 --> 00:36:05,024
And so it'll <i>be...</i>

656
00:36:05,129 --> 00:36:07,757
You know, we'll come up,
and then we won't be up here

657
00:36:07,865 --> 00:36:11,699
for another, you know,
maybe a week or two.

658
00:36:11,802 --> 00:36:14,965
And then there's been
times where, you know,

659
00:36:15,072 --> 00:36:19,065
I've had enough pain medicine
to get off of the other stuff

660
00:36:19,177 --> 00:36:22,010
and gone a month
without the other.

661
00:36:22,113 --> 00:36:23,580
And then you run out of that,

662
00:36:23,681 --> 00:36:25,205
and then you get sucked
right back into it

663
00:36:25,316 --> 00:36:27,910
because you just can't break
that cycle of being sick

664
00:36:28,019 --> 00:36:30,317
and getting off of opiates,
you know?

665
00:36:33,324 --> 00:36:35,622
Maybe I always haven't been
the best husband,

666
00:36:35,726 --> 00:36:36,852
but my kids love me.

667
00:36:36,961 --> 00:36:39,020
If somebody were
to take me today, you know,

668
00:36:39,130 --> 00:36:41,325
one thing that I do know
will be said about me is that

669
00:36:41,432 --> 00:36:43,263
"the guy was
a really great dad."

670
00:36:43,367 --> 00:36:45,198
And that's one thing
I'm absolutely proud of.

671
00:36:45,303 --> 00:36:46,292
That's what I live for.

672
00:36:46,404 --> 00:36:48,929
I think the biggest toll
that it's taken,

673
00:36:49,040 --> 00:36:50,871
just if you want to
look at financially,

674
00:36:50,975 --> 00:36:54,706
is losing about
a $500, 000-a-year job

675
00:36:54,812 --> 00:36:55,972
because of my addiction.

676
00:36:56,080 --> 00:36:57,206
Just going out there

677
00:36:57,315 --> 00:37:00,842
and either running out
of medication to take

678
00:37:00,952 --> 00:37:03,147
and getting so sick
that I couldn't perform my job.

679
00:37:03,254 --> 00:37:05,518
And then kind of
getting labeled that way

680
00:37:05,690 --> 00:37:07,214
and people not wanting
to take a risk

681
00:37:07,325 --> 00:37:09,054
on somebody that has a problem

682
00:37:09,160 --> 00:37:11,856
and will have somebody else
in here that is not a high risk.

683
00:37:11,963 --> 00:37:13,362
So it's had a huge effect.

684
00:37:13,464 --> 00:37:15,295
When my kids get up
early in the morning

685
00:37:15,399 --> 00:37:16,798
after sleeping well at night

686
00:37:16,901 --> 00:37:19,165
and I've been up all night
'cause I don't sleep well,

687
00:37:19,270 --> 00:37:22,330
and they're bouncing off the
walls and excited to do stuff,

688
00:37:22,440 --> 00:37:25,136
and I don't have the energy to
get up and do stuff with them...

689
00:37:25,243 --> 00:37:26,767
Are you kidding me?

690
00:37:26,877 --> 00:37:28,139
You know how much that sucks

691
00:37:28,246 --> 00:37:30,180
to have them wondering,
"What's wrong with Dad?

692
00:37:30,281 --> 00:37:32,044
Why can't he come out
and do stuff with us?"

693
00:37:32,149 --> 00:37:33,275
Once you get to that point,

694
00:37:33,384 --> 00:37:35,215
you will do anything
to get out of it.

695
00:37:35,319 --> 00:37:36,752
Anything.

696
00:37:36,854 --> 00:37:38,947
We called one of these places

697
00:37:39,056 --> 00:37:42,321
for detox and rehab
and all that, you know?

698
00:37:42,426 --> 00:37:45,088
And some of them
are pretty pricey.

699
00:37:45,196 --> 00:37:48,256
And you got to go in there with
money up front and all of this.

700
00:37:48,366 --> 00:37:50,766
And so I honestly did not know
what to do.

701
00:37:50,868 --> 00:37:53,029
Is it cheaper to stay on drugs?

702
00:37:53,137 --> 00:37:55,332
Oh, yeah.
Absolutely.

703
00:37:55,439 --> 00:37:58,966
Not only, I mean, just the
financial side of things.

704
00:37:59,076 --> 00:38:00,805
You can have a pretty bad habit

705
00:38:00,911 --> 00:38:03,243
and do it
relatively inexpensively.

706
00:38:03,347 --> 00:38:05,679
Or, I mean, thousands
and thousands of dollars

707
00:38:05,850 --> 00:38:08,910
for detox and rehab
and all that.

708
00:38:09,020 --> 00:38:11,420
And, unfortunately,
a lot of these places,

709
00:38:11,522 --> 00:38:13,251
they don't work for people

710
00:38:13,357 --> 00:38:15,052
because they go in
with the wrong reasons.

711
00:38:15,159 --> 00:38:17,389
And especially in this valley,
there's this mentality that,

712
00:38:17,495 --> 00:38:19,861
if somebody's got a problem,
we'll drop them off and say,

713
00:38:19,997 --> 00:38:22,022
"Make them better,
and we'll be back in a bit."

714
00:38:22,133 --> 00:38:24,101
You know?
And it doesn't work that way.

715
00:38:24,201 --> 00:38:26,192
So we come out
of the gas station.

716
00:38:26,304 --> 00:38:28,431
We've been praying, looking for
an answer what to do.

717
00:38:28,539 --> 00:38:31,235
I see this sign..."Addicted?
<i>Drugs...</i> Prescriptions?

718
00:38:31,342 --> 00:38:35,972
We sponsor recovery!
Happy Valley. Confidential."

719
00:38:36,080 --> 00:38:38,173
So I come out.

720
00:38:38,282 --> 00:38:39,749
Come out of the gas station

721
00:38:39,850 --> 00:38:42,751
after literally having been
fighting with my wife,

722
00:38:42,853 --> 00:38:45,185
praying what can I do,
and I see this sign that says,

723
00:38:45,289 --> 00:38:47,450
"Happy Valley Detox.
Confidential."

724
00:38:47,558 --> 00:38:51,289
And on the way up to the city,

725
00:38:51,395 --> 00:38:54,887
was on my cellphone
calling your number.

